title: For Sale:  Steyr M95 Rifle , cal. 8x56R
postcontent: This Steyr M95 straight pull bolt action rifle is one of many refurbished by Bulguria after World War 1 ended. After the war the Austro- Hungarian Empire was dissolved and its armies disbanded by the Allies. Many of the original Steyr M95 long rifles were taken over by the Balkan countries, including Bulgaria. The Bulgarians shortened the barrel and attached cavarly carbine swivels to the stock. The result was a rough looking weapon but it was perfectly shootable and easier to handle than the original. Shot this one at the range a few times and it wasn't a bad shooter. An impulse buy for me but now I have an Austrian made M95 long rifle in the original 8x50R calibre and this one is just taking up safe space.Price includes two 20 round boxes of 8x56R ammo ( 203gr FMJ and SP ) and two Austrian made ( c. 1934 ) 5 round M95 en bloc clips.
